#: ./security-guide/section_tls-proxies-and-http-services.xml:279(para)
msgid "We recommend that all production deployments use HTTP strict transport security (HSTS). This header prevents browsers from making insecure connections after they have made a single secure one. If you have deployed your HTTP services on a public or an untrusted domain, HSTS is especially important. To enable HSTS, configure your web server to send a header like this with all requests:"
