#: ./security-guide/section_networking-architecture.xml:9(para)
msgid "OpenStack Networking is a standalone service that often deploys several processes across a number of nodes. These processes interact with each other and other OpenStack services. The main process of the OpenStack Networking service is <systemitem class=\"service\">neutron-server</systemitem>, a Python daemon that exposes the OpenStack Networking API and passes tenant requests to a suite of plug-ins for additional processing."
